Definition.WordDefinition:
Type \Type\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Typed}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Typing}.] 1. To represent by a type, model, or symbol beforehand; to prefigure. [R.] --White (Johnson). [1913 Webster]
2. To furnish an expression or copy of; to represent; to typify. [R.] [1913 Webster]
Let us type them now in our own lives. --Tennyson. [1913 Webster]
typed adj : written on a typewriter [syn: {typewritten}]
